{"batch":"error_consistency","batch_index":3,"assessments":{"error_consistency":43.0},"dimension_notes":{"error_consistency":{"evidence":["The season-wide collector in calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py mixes several failure contracts for similar network/data boundaries: season_exists() returns False on any exception (lines 32-38), game_exists() returns False after retries (lines 41-52), fetch_game_json_with_retry() converts both HTTP status handling and any thrown exception into the string status \"missing\" with no error object (lines 69-85), and process_game() adds a third contract by returning {\"status\": \"error\"} when parsing/computation fails (lines 156-174).","The single-game scripts fail fast on the same kind of I/O boundary instead of normalizing to sentinel values: build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py calls requests.get(...), then response.raise_for_status(), and lets malformed game structure raise ValueError (lines 63-80); categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py and step2_build_possessions.py do the same (categorize lines 66-82, step2 lines 131-140 and 48-49).","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py preserves the last network exception in fetch_json_with_retry() and re-raises it (lines 29-39), but the caller immediately broad-catches future.result() failures and collapses them to failed_ids with no message or cause (lines 128-153), so the repository has no consistent policy for whether to preserve error context or reduce failures to bookkeeping.","The helper parse_int() in build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py and categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py catches Exception and returns None for any conversion problem (build lines 22-28, categorize lines 22-28), while other invalid-shape checks in the same scripts raise ValueError instead (build lines 78-80, categorize lines 80-82). That makes bad input sometimes silent and sometimes fatal depending on which path touches it first."],"impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","confidence":"high"}},"issues":[{"dimension":"error_consistency","identifier":"season_jobs_swallow_root_errors","summary":"Season aggregation scripts collapse network and parse failures into booleans or \"missing\" states without preserving the original cause.","related_files":["calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py"],"evidence":["calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py season_exists() catches any Exception and returns False, so a timeout, DNS failure, or JSON bug is indistinguishable from a season that does not exist (lines 32-38).","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py fetch_game_json_with_retry() catches any Exception and returns (\"missing\", None) after retries, which erases whether the problem was a transport failure, decode failure, or unexpected response shape (lines 69-85).","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py initially preserves the last exception in fetch_json_with_retry(), but main() then catches Exception around future.result() and retry processing and only appends the game_id to failed_ids, dropping the exception context before reporting (lines 128-153)."],"suggestion":"Define one failure model for season jobs: either raise a typed exception with game_id/season context, or return a structured error object that includes category and original message. Keep missing-game cases separate from transient/network/parsing failures.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"subsystem","fix_scope":"multi_file_refactor","root_cause_cluster":"ad_hoc_error_contracts"},{"dimension":"error_consistency","identifier":"same_boundary_different_error_policy","summary":"Scripts that all fetch NBA play-by-play data use incompatible error strategies at the same I/O boundary.","related_files":["build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py","step2_build_possessions.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py"],"evidence":["build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py, categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py, and step2_build_possessions.py all call requests.get(...), then response.raise_for_status(), and let failures terminate the run immediately (build lines 63-67, categorize lines 66-70, step2 lines 131-136).","By contrast, calculate_wmi_rawseason_2010_11_to_2023_24.py treats similar request failures as availability probes or missing games and keeps going via False / \"missing\" / {\"status\": \"missing\"} returns (lines 32-38, 41-52, 69-85, 156-164).","calculate_wmi_rawseason_2024_25.py uses a third variant: network calls raise from fetch_json_with_retry(), but higher-level orchestration demotes them back into failed_ids bookkeeping (lines 29-39, 128-153)."],"suggestion":"Extract a shared fetch layer for NBA play-by-play access with one explicit contract, such as raising domain-specific exceptions (`GameMissing`, `TransientFetchError`, `InvalidPayload`) and letting each script decide only at the top level whether to stop or continue.","confidence":"high","impact_scope":"codebase","fix_scope":"architectural_change","root_cause_cluster":"ad_hoc_error_contracts"},{"dimension":"error_consistency","identifier":"parse_helpers_silently_hide_bad_values","summary":"`parse_int` silently converts any conversion error to `None`, while nearby validation paths raise explicit exceptions.","related_files":["build_possession_model_table_okc_mil.py","categorize_defensive_fouls_okc_mil.py"],"evidence":["Both files define parse_int() with `except Exception: return None` around `int(value)` (build lines 22-28, categorize lines 22-28), so invalid score fields are quietly treated as missing data.","In the same modules, structural validation uses explicit `ValueError` when the game does not resolve to exactly two teams (build lines 78-80, categorize lines 80-82), which means malformed upstream data is sometimes surfaced and sometimes silently ignored.","Because score parsing failures turn into `None`, downstream calculations like `score_difference` simply stay `None` instead of exposing that the source row was malformed (build lines 105-114, categorize lines 130-146)."],"suggestion":"Narrow these handlers to the expected conversion exceptions and decide one policy for malformed score fields: either raise a descriptive data-validation error or return a typed missing-value result that callers must handle explicitly.","confidence":"medium","impact_scope":"module","fix_scope":"single_edit","root_cause_cluster":"ad_hoc_error_contracts"}],"retrospective":{"root_causes":["Scripts appear to have been built independently, so each one invented its own failure contract at network and parsing boundaries.","Retry logic was added for robustness, but without a shared error model it now hides important diagnostic context."],"likely_symptoms":["season_jobs_swallow_root_errors","same_boundary_different_error_policy","parse_helpers_silently_hide_bad_values"],"possible_false_positives":["The blind packet did not include holistic_context.errors.exception_hotspots; only strategy_by_directory was present, so hotspot guidance was unavailable for this batch."]}}
